{'task': 'Software Development Task:\n\nPlease write a software application called AstroSim, which simulates and visualizes astronomical phenomena such as planetary orbits, stellar evolution, and galactic dynamics. AstroSim is a comprehensive simulation tool that allows users to input parameters for celestial bodies and environmental conditions, and observe the resulting simulations in real-time. The application also provides educational content and interactive features to enhance user understanding of complex astronomical concepts.\n\n1. Implementation requirements:\n\n2. Project structure:\n   - solution.py (main implementation)\n\n3. Development process:\n   - Developer: Create the code.\n   - Developer: Revise the code.\n   - Developer: Optimize the code.\n\nPlease work together to complete this task following software engineering best practices.', 'coordination_mode': 'graph', 'iterations': [{'iteration': 1, 'task_assignments': {'agent1': 'Software Development Task:\n\nPlease write a software application called AstroSim, which simulates and visualizes astronomical phenomena such as planetary orbits, stellar evolution, and galactic dynamics. AstroSim is a comprehensive simulation tool that allows users to input parameters for celestial bodies and environmental conditions, and observe the resulting simulations in real-time. The application also provides educational content and interactive features to enhance user understanding of complex astronomical concepts.\n\n1. Implementation requirements:\n\n2. Project structure:\n   - solution.py (main implementation)\n\n3. Development process:\n   - Developer: Create the code.\n   - Developer: Revise the code.\n   - Developer: Optimize the code.\n\nPlease work together to complete this task following software engineering best practices.', 'agent2': 'Software Development Task:\n\nPlease write a software application called AstroSim, which simulates and visualizes astronomical phenomena such as planetary orbits, stellar evolution, and galactic dynamics. AstroSim is a comprehensive simulation tool that allows users to input parameters for celestial bodies and environmental conditions, and observe the resulting simulations in real-time. The application also provides educational content and interactive features to enhance user understanding of complex astronomical concepts.\n\n1. Implementation requirements:\n\n2. Project structure:\n   - solution.py (main implementation)\n\n3. Development process:\n   - Developer: Create the code.\n   - Developer: Revise the code.\n   - Developer: Optimize the code.\n\nPlease work together to complete this task following software engineering best practices.', 'agent3': 'Software Development Task:\n\nPlease write a software application called AstroSim, which simulates and visualizes astronomical phenomena such as planetary orbits, stellar evolution, and galactic dynamics. AstroSim is a comprehensive simulation tool that allows users to input parameters for celestial bodies and environmental conditions, and observe the resulting simulations in real-time. The application also provides educational content and interactive features to enhance user understanding of complex astronomical concepts.\n\n1. Implementation requirements:\n\n2. Project structure:\n   - solution.py (main implementation)\n\n3. Development process:\n   - Developer: Create the code.\n   - Developer: Revise the code.\n   - Developer: Optimize the code.\n\nPlease work together to complete this task following software engineering best practices.'}, 'task_results': [{'agent_id': 'agent1', 'result': 'Result from the model:\nResult from the function:{"success": true, "message": "Solution file created at C:\\\\Users\\\\70454\\\\Desktop\\\\PredictDesign\\\\results\\\\parallel_api_test\\\\runtime_configs\\\\coding\\\\task_45_workspace\\\\solution.py", "code": "# solution.py\\n\\nclass CollaborativeBuildOptimizer:\\n    \\"\\"\\"\\n    The Collaborative Build Optimizer (CBO) class is designed to enhance the build process\\n    for software projects by integrating code efficiency analysis, task management, and build\\n    time estimation. This class provides methods to analyze code, manage tasks, and estimate\\n    build times.\\n    \\"\\"\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Initialize the CollaborativeBuildOptimizer with empty data structures for tasks and code analysis.\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        self.tasks = {}  # Dictionary to store tasks with their dependencies\\n        self.code_efficiency = {}  # Dictionary to store code efficiency metrics\\n\\n    def add_task(self, task_id, dependencies=None):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Add a new task to the task manager with optional dependencies.\\n\\n        :param task_id: Unique identifier for the task.\\n        :param dependencies: List of task IDs that this task depends on.\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        if dependencies is None:\\n            dependencies = []\\n        self.tasks[task_id] = dependencies\\n\\n    def analyze_code(self, code_snippet):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Analyze a code snippet for efficiency. This is a simplified example that counts the number of lines\\n        as a proxy for code efficiency. In a real-world scenario, this could involve more complex analysis.\\n\\n        :param code_snippet: String containing the code to be analyzed.\\n        :return: Efficiency metric (e.g., number of lines).\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        lines = code_snippet.split(\'\\\\n\')\\n        efficiency_metric = len(lines)\\n        self.code_efficiency[code_snippet] = efficiency_metric\\n        return efficiency_metric\\n\\n    def estimate_build_time(self):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Estimate the build time based on the number of tasks and their dependencies. This is a simplified\\n        example that assumes each task takes a fixed amount of time plus additional time for each dependency.\\n\\n        :return: Estimated build time in arbitrary units.\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        base_time_per_task = 10  # Base time to complete a task\\n        dependency_time = 5  # Additional time for each dependency\\n\\n        total_time = 0\\n        for task_id, dependencies in self.tasks.items():\\n            total_time += base_time_per_task + (len(dependencies) * dependency_time)\\n\\n        return total_time\\n\\n    def get_task_order(self):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Determine the order in which tasks should be executed based on their dependencies using a topological sort.\\n\\n        :return: List of task IDs in the order they should be executed.\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        from collections import deque\\n\\n        # Calculate in-degrees for each task\\n        in_degree = {task_id: 0 for task_id in self.tasks}\\n        for task_id, dependencies in self.tasks.items():\\n            for dependency in dependencies:\\n                in_degree[dependency] += 1\\n\\n        # Initialize queue with tasks that have no dependencies\\n        queue = deque([task_id for task_id, degree in in_degree.items() if degree == 0])\\n        task_order = []\\n\\n        while queue:\\n            task_id = queue.popleft()\\n            task_order.append(task_id)\\n            for dependent_task in self.tasks:\\n                if task_id in self.tasks[dependent_task]:\\n                    in_degree[dependent_task] -= 1\\n                    if in_degree[dependent_task] == 0:\\n                        queue.append(dependent_task)\\n\\n        return task_order\\n\\n# Example usage\\nif __name__ == \\"__main__\\":\\n    cbo = CollaborativeBuildOptimizer()\\n\\n    # Adding tasks with dependencies\\n    cbo.add_task(\'task1\')\\n    cbo.add_task(\'task2\', [\'task1\'])\\n    cbo.add_task(\'task3\', [\'task1\'])\\n    cbo.add_task(\'task4\', [\'task2\', \'task3\'])\\n\\n    # Analyzing code snippets\\n    code_snippet1 = \\"def add(a, b):\\\\n    return a + b\\"\\n    code_snippet2 = \\"def multiply(a, b):\\\\n    return a * b\\"\\n    cbo.analyze_code(code_snippet1)\\n    cbo.analyze_code(code_snippet2)\\n\\n    # Estimating build time\\n    build_time = cbo.estimate_build_time()\\n    print(f\\"Estimated build time: {build_time} units\\")\\n\\n    # Getting task order\\n    task_order = cbo.get_task_order()\\n    print(f\\"Task order: {task_order}\\")"}'}, {'agent_id': 'agent2', 'result': 'Result from the model:\nResult from the function:{"success": true, "message": "Successfully completed session 926f3648-8b5e-4e6a-bbab-18c97ddbf5da", "full_chat_history": "In Session 926f3648-8b5e-4e6a-bbab-18c97ddbf5da \\nFrom agent2 to agent1: Hi agent1, I am ready to start working on the AstroSim project. Please create the initial code framework based on the task description and requirements.\\n", "session_id": "### Summary of Chat History: AstroSim Project\\n\\n**Context and Participants:**\\n- **Agent1:** Developer responsible for creating, revising, and optimizing the code.\\n- **Agent2:** Initiator of the project, requesting the initial code framework.\\n\\n**Task Overview:**\\nThe task is to develop a software application named AstroSim, which simulates and visualizes various astronomical phenomena, including planetary orbits, stellar evolution, and galactic dynamics. The application should allow users to input parameters and observe simulations in real-time, while also providing educational content and interactive features.\\n\\n**Key Points and Themes:**\\n1. **Project Structure:**\\n   - The main implementation file is named `solution.py`.\\n\\n2. **Development Process:**\\n   - **Step 1:** Agent1 is tasked with creating the initial code framework.\\n   - **Step 2:** Agent1 will revise the code to ensure it meets the requirements and standards.\\n   - **Step 3:** Agent1 will optimize the code for performance and efficiency.\\n\\n3. **Software Engineering Best Practices:**\\n   - The development process emphasizes adherence to best practices in software engineering, including code creation, revision, and optimization.\\n\\n**Actions and Outcomes:**\\n- **Agent2\'s Request:** Agent2 initiated the conversation by requesting Agent1 to start working on the AstroSim project and to create the initial code framework based on the provided task description and requirements.\\n- **Next Steps:** The immediate action is for Agent1 to begin the development process by creating the initial code framework in `solution.py`.\\n\\n**Conclusion:**\\nThe conversation sets the stage for the development of the AstroSim project, with clear expectations and a structured approach to ensure the application meets the specified requirements and adheres to software engineering best practices. The next step is for Agent1 to start the initial code development.\\n\\nIf you have any specific interests or need further details on any part of the conversation, feel free to let me know!"}'}, {'agent_id': 'agent3', 'result': 'Result from the model:\nResult from the function:{"success": true, "task_aspects": {"implementation": 0, "testing": 0, "optimization": 1, "debugging": 0, "documentation": 0}, "complexity_score": 0.2, "primary_focus": "optimization"}'}], 'summary': 'Based on the provided results from the agents, it seems there is a mismatch between the expected output and the actual results. The task was to create a software application called AstroSim, but the provided code snippet from `agent1` does not seem to align with the project requirements. Instead, it appears to be a class for a build optimizer, which is unrelated to the AstroSim project.\n\nHere is a revised and simplified version of `solution.py` that aligns with the project requirements. This version will include a basic structure for the AstroSim application, which can be expanded upon in future iterations.\n\n```json\n{\n  "solution.py": "# solution.py\\n\\nimport numpy as np\\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\nfrom scipy.integrate import solve_ivp\\n\\nclass AstroSim:\\n    \\"\\"\\"\\n    The AstroSim class is designed to simulate and visualize various astronomical phenomena.\\n    \\"\\"\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Initialize the AstroSim with default parameters.\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        self.planets = []\\n        self.stars = []\\n        self.galaxies = []\\n\\n    def add_planet(self, name, mass, position, velocity):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Add a planet to the simulation.\\n        :param name: Name of the planet\\n        :param mass: Mass of the planet\\n        :param position: Initial position of the planet\\n        :param velocity: Initial velocity of the planet\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        self.planets.append({\'name\': name, \'mass\': mass, \'position\': np.array(position), \'velocity\': np.array(velocity)})\\n\\n    def add_star(self, name, mass, position, velocity):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Add a star to the simulation.\\n        :param name: Name of the star\\n        :param mass: Mass of the star\\n        :param position: Initial position of the star\\n        :param velocity: Initial velocity of the star\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        self.stars.append({\'name\': name, \'mass\': mass, \'position\': np.array(position), \'velocity\': np.array(velocity)})\\n\\n    def add_galaxy(self, name, mass, position, velocity):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Add a galaxy to the simulation.\\n        :param name: Name of the galaxy\\n        :param mass: Mass of the galaxy\\n        :param position: Initial position of the galaxy\\n        :param velocity: Initial velocity of the galaxy\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        self.galaxies.append({\'name\': name, \'mass\': mass, \'position\': np.array(position), \'velocity\': np.array(velocity)})\\n\\n    def simulate(self, t_span, t_eval):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Simulate the motion of celestial bodies over a specified time span.\\n        :param t_span: Tuple of start and end times for the simulation\\n        :param t_eval: Times at which to store the computed solution\\n        :return: Solution object containing the positions and velocities of celestial bodies\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        y0 = []\\n        for body in self.planets + self.stars + self.galaxies:\\n            y0.extend(body[\'position\'])\\n            y0.extend(body[\'velocity\'])\\n\\n        sol = solve_ivp(self._derivatives, t_span, y0, t_eval=t_eval)\\n        return sol\\n\\n    def _derivatives(self, t, y):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Compute the derivatives of the positions and velocities of celestial bodies.\\n        :param t: Current time\\n        :param y: Current state vector (positions and velocities)\\n        :return: Derivatives of the state vector\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        n = len(self.planets) + len(self.stars) + len(self.galaxies)\\n        dydt = np.zeros_like(y)\\n        positions = y[:2*n].reshape(-1, 2)\\n        velocities = y[2*n:].reshape(-1, 2)\\n\\n        for i in range(n):\\n            dydt[2*i:2*i+2] = velocities[i]\\n            for j in range(n):\\n                if i != j:\\n                    r = positions[j] - positions[i]\\n                    r_norm = np.linalg.norm(r)\\n                    dydt[2*n+2*i:2*n+2*i+2] += r * (self._get_mass(j) / r_norm**3)\\n\\n        return dydt\\n\\n    def _get_mass(self, index):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Get the mass of a celestial body by index.\\n        :param index: Index of the celestial body\\n        :return: Mass of the celestial body\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        if index < len(self.planets):\\n            return self.planets[index][\'mass\']\\n        elif index < len(self.planets) + len(self.stars):\\n            return self.stars[index - len(self.planets)][\'mass\']\\n        else:\\n            return self.galaxies[index - len(self.planets) - len(self.stars)][\'mass\']\\n\\n    def visualize(self, sol):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Visualize the simulation results.\\n        :param sol: Solution object containing the positions and velocities of celestial bodies\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        n = len(self.planets) + len(self.stars) + len(self.galaxies)\\n        positions = sol.y[:2*n].reshape(-1, 2, sol.t.size)\\n\\n        plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))\\n        for i in range(n):\\n            plt.plot(positions[i, 0], positions[i, 1], label=f\'Body {i+1}\')\\n        plt.title(\'AstroSim Simulation\')\\n        plt.xlabel(\'X Position\')\\n        plt.ylabel(\'Y Position\')\\n        plt.legend()\\n        plt.grid(True)\\n        plt.show()\\n\\n# Example usage:\\nif __name__ == \'__main__\':\\n    sim = AstroSim()\\n    sim.add_planet(\'Earth\', 1, [1, 0], [0, 1])\\n    sim.add_star(\'Sun\', 100, [0, 0], [0, 0])\\n    sol = sim.simulate([0, 10], np.linspace(0, 10, 100))\\n    sim.visualize(sol)\\n"\n}\n```\n\nThis code provides a basic framework for the AstroSim application, including methods to add celestial bodies, simulate their motion, and visualize the results. It can be expanded with more features and optimizations as required.', 'continue_simulation': True, 'communications': ['In Session 926f3648-8b5e-4e6a-bbab-18c97ddbf5da \nFrom agent2 to agent1: Hi agent1, I am ready to start working on the AstroSim project. Please create the initial code framework based on the task description and requirements.\n']}, {'iteration': 2, 'task_assignments': {'agent1': 'Given your role as a Senior Software Developer specialized in Python development and your strengths and weaknesses, the next task should be to create the initial code framework for the AstroSim application. Since you are good at creating the code framework from scratch based on the task description and requirements, you should call the `create_code` action.\n\nHere\'s the next step:\n\n1. **Create the initial code framework for AstroSim**:\n   - You will create the basic structure and initial implementation of the AstroSim application.\n   - This includes setting up the main components such as the simulation engine, visualization module, and user interface.\n\nSince you have already created a `solution.py` file, you should now focus on fleshing out the initial code for AstroSim within that file. Here is an example of how you might structure the initial code:\n\n```python\n# solution.py\n\nclass AstroSim:\n    """\n    The AstroSim class is designed to simulate and visualize astronomical phenomena\n    such as planetary orbits, stellar evolution, and galactic dynamics.\n    """\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        """\n        Initialize the AstroSim with default parameters and settings.\n        """\n        self.parameters = {}\n        self.simulation_results = None\n\n    def set_parameters(self, parameters):\n        """\n        Set the parameters for the simulation.\n\n        :param parameters: Dictionary containing the parameters for celestial bodies and environmental conditions.\n        """\n        self.parameters = parameters\n\n    def run_simulation(self):\n        """\n        Run the simulation based on the set parameters.\n\n        :return: Simulation results.\n        """\n        # Placeholder for the actual simulation logic\n        self.simulation_results = "Simulation results based on parameters"\n        return self.simulation_results\n\n    def visualize(self):\n        """\n        Visualize the simulation results.\n\n        :return: Visualization of the simulation results.\n        """\n        # Placeholder for the actual visualization logic\n        visualization = "Visualization of simulation results"\n        return visualization\n\n    def provide_educational_content(self):\n        """\n        Provide educational content related to the simulation.\n\n        :return: Educational content.\n        """\n        # Placeholder for the actual educational content logic\n        educational_content = "Educational content about the simulation"\n        return educational_content\n\n# Example usage\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    astro_sim = AstroSim()\n    astro_sim.set_parameters({"planet": "Earth", "star": "Sun", "galaxy":